addModule(address).details: Only callable by authorized address.Fails if address invalid or address already added as module.

returns._0: The return data of the call.

returns._1: The return data of the call.

returns._0: True if module added, false otherwise.

removeModule(address).details: Only callable by authorized address.Fails if address not added as module.

params.authorizer_: The address of the new authorizer module.

params.fundingManager_: The address of the new funding manager module.

params.paymentProcessor_: The address of the new payment processor module.

trustedForwarder().details: Returns the address of the trusted forwarder.

authorizer().notice: The {IAuthorizer} implementation used to authorize addresses.

executeTx(address,bytes).notice: Executes a call on target `target` with call data `data`.

executeTxFromModule(address,bytes).notice: Executes a call to `to` with call data `data` either via call

findModuleAddressInOrchestrator(string).notice: find the address of a given module using it's name in a orchestrator

fundingManager().notice: The {IFundingManager} implementation used to hold and distribute Funds.

isModule(address).notice: Returns whether the address `module` is added as module.

listModules().notice: Returns the list of all modules.

paymentProcessor().notice: The {IPaymentProcessor} implementation used to process module         payments.

setFundingManager(address).notice: Replaces the current funding manager with `fundingManager_`

setPaymentProcessor(address).notice: Replaces the current payment processor with `paymentProcessor_`

version().notice: The version of the orchestrator instance.
